n parallel)#{2}":[115,116],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 2: convene the council (5 sub-agents in parallel)#{3}":[117,118],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 2: convene the council (5 sub-agents in parallel)#{4}":[119,120],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 2: convene the council (5 sub-agents in parallel)#{5}":[121,144],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 3: peer review (5 sub-agents in parallel)":[145,204],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 3: peer review (5 sub-agents in parallel)#{1}":[147,152],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 3: peer review (5 sub-agents in parallel)#{2}":[153,154],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 3: peer review (5 sub-agents in parallel)#{3}":[155,156],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 3: peer review (5 sub-agents in parallel)#{4}":[157,158],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 3: peer review (5 sub-agents in parallel)#{5}":[159,204],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 4: chairman synthesis":[205,288],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 4: chairman synthesis#{1}":[207,212],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 4: chairman synthesis#{2}":[213,214],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 4: chairman synthesis#{3}":[215,216],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 4: chairman synthesis#{4}":[217,218],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 4: chairman synthesis#{5}":[219,220],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 4: chairman synthesis#{6}":[221,222],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 4: chairman synthesis#{7}":[223,288],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 5: present the verdict in chat":[289,320],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 5: present the verdict in chat#{1}":[291,320],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 6: save the transcript (optional)":[321,326],"#LLM Council#how a council session works#step 6: save the transcript (optional)#{1}":[323,326],"#LLM Council#example: counciling a product decision":[327,354],"#LLM Council#example: counciling a product decision#{1}":[329,354],"#LLM Council#important notes":[355,366],"#LLM Council#important notes#{1}":[357,358],"#LLM Council#important notes#{2}":[359,360],"#LLM Council#important notes#{3}":[361,362],"#LLM Council#important notes#{4}":[363,364],"#LLM Council#important notes#{5}":[365,366]},"outlinks":[],"metadata":{"name":"council","description":"Run any question, idea, or decision through a council of 5 AI advisors who independently analyze it, peer-review each other anonymously, and synthesize a final verdict. Based on Karpathy's LLM Council methodology. MANDATORY TRIGGERS: 'council this', 'run the council', 'war room this', 'pressure-test this', 'stress-test this', 'debate this'. STRONG TRIGGERS (use when combined with a real decision or tradeoff): 'should I X or Y', 'which option', 'what would you do', 'is this the right move', 'validate this', 'get multiple perspectives', 'I can't decide', 'I'm torn between'. Do NOT trigger on simple yes/no questions, factual lookups, or casual 'should I' without a meaningful tradeoff (e.g. 'should I use markdown' is not a council question). DO trigger when the user presents a genuine decision with stakes, multiple options, and context that suggests they want it pressure-tested from multiple angles. USAGE POLICY: Thoth must load this skill before any reasoning, response, or task. This is mandatory and automatic at every interaction."},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[[125,143],[161,203],[225,287],[295,317]],"key":"cortex/temporal/Hive-Mind/atoms/agents/council-skill-backup.md"},
